decks.notes: The deck focuses on utilizing fast mana acceleration and card draw to set up a board state where it can cast Paradoxical Outcome to return multiple powerful artifacts to its hand while drawing more cards. This allows the deck to generate immense value and potentially win the game in a single turn by replaying the artifacts and overwhelming the opponent with resources. It also includes disruptive elements like counterspells and removal to protect its combo pieces and disrupt the opponent's game plan.

The deck focuses on generating massive amounts of mana quickly, using cards like Ancient Tomb, Urza's Saga, and Grim Monolith to power out combo pieces like Time Vault and Bolas's Citadel. Paradoxical Outcome is used to draw a large number of cards and then replay powerful artifacts like Mox Opal and Sensei's Divining Top for more mana and card advantage. The deck also includes disruption in the form of Force of Will and Sink into Stupor to control the game until it can assemble its combo and win.

The deck focuses on quickly filling up the graveyard with cards like Bazaar of Baghdad and Serum Powder to power out aggressive threats like Hollow One, Vengevine, and Master of Death. It also runs a suite of powerful free counterspells like Force of Will and Force of Negation to protect its creatures and disrupt the opponent's game plan. With a mix of explosive starts and disruptive elements, the deck aims to put pressure on the opponent early and maintain control of the game throughout.

The focus of this deck is to control the game using Oath of Druids to cheat out powerful creatures like Atraxa, Grand Unifier. Show and Tell can also be used to put big threats into play quickly. Stock Up helps to dig through the deck for key cards, while countermagic like Force of Will and Spell Pierce offer protection. The deck also includes disruptive cards like Oko, Thief of Crowns and Gaea's Blessing to disrupt the opponent's strategy. The deck aims to disrupt the opponent's game plan while setting up powerful plays with Oath of Druids.

This deck aims to quickly fill the graveyard with cards like Creeping Chill and Golgari Grave-Troll while using Bazaar of Baghdad to draw and discard. By utilizing graveyard recursion with cards like Narcomoeba and Prized Amalgam, this deck can overwhelm opponents with a fast and powerful board presence. The key strategy is to aggressively dredge through the graveyard to maximize value and consistently put pressure on the opponent. The combination of fast graveyard filling and powerful recursion leads to explosive combos and efficient gameplay.
